{"questionId":"9077105","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The <em>pV</em> diagram of a heat engine using an ideal gas consists of an isothermal expansion&nbsp;A → B, an isobaric compression B → C and an adiabatic compression C → A.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/5cc3b96e169a5f10d34e53ac277d43625b9dfc4a.png\"></p>\n<p>The following data are available:</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:180px;\">Temperature at A&nbsp; &nbsp;= 385 K</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:180px;\">Pressure at A&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;= 2.80 × 10<sup>6 </sup>Pa</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:180px;\">Volume at A&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;= 1.00 × 10<sup>–4 </sup>m<sup>3</sup></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:180px;\">Volume at B&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;= 2.80 × 10<sup>–4 </sup>m<sup>3</sup></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:180px;\">Volume at C&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;= 1.85 × 10<sup>–4 </sup>m<sup>3</sup></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>The work done by the gas from A → B is 288 J. Calculate the efficiency of&nbsp;the cycle.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>net work is 288 −238 = 50 «J» ✔</p>\n<p>efficiency =&nbsp;«<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{288 - 238}}{{288}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>288</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>238</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>288</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;=»&nbsp;0.17 ✔</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9077105","referenceCode":"18N.3.SL.TZ0.7c.i","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"The work done by the gas from A → B is 288 J. Calculate the efficiency of the cycle.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics (Core topics)","B.2 – Thermodynamics","Option B: Engineering physics","Optio